; 6 Form, (1970 &#8211; 1976).<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><strong>Career<\/strong><\/td>\n<td>Swapo Party Regional Coordinator, Oshana Region (1998 &#8211; 2010); Swapo Party Regional Mobiliser Oshana Region (1993 &#8211; 1998); Swapo Party Oshakati District Mobiliser in Oshana Region (1992 &#8211; 1993); Ex \u2013 Combatant Representatives in Oshana Region, (1995 &#8211; 1996); Reporter and Photographer, Namibia Today (Swapo a bi-weekly newspaper) in Oshakati, (1989 &#8211; 1991); Photographer for Namibia Today (Swapo monthly organ) in Lubango, Angola (1985 &#8211; 1989); Commander, First Mechanized Infantry Brigade in Lubango Angola; Joined People\u2019s Liberation Army of Namibia (PLAN) (1979); Military Training (6 month) Tobias Hainyeko Military Training Centre Lubango, Angola (1979).<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Legislative Interests<\/strong><\/td>\n<td>Legal; ICT; Trade; Urban and Rural Development Issues.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Minister: Urban &amp; Rural Development SWAPO Party Legislative Profile Member of the National Assembly; Minister of Sport, Youth and National Services\u00a0 since February 2018; Deputy Minister of Home Affairs and Immigration, (2015 -2018); Member of the National Assembly, Deputy Minister of Safety and Security, (2010 &#8211; 2015) Personal Born on 29 January 1961, Omatando, Oshana&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":2375,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","dt_team_category":[105,104,92],"class_list":["post-2374","dt_team","type-dt_team","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","dt_team_category-5th-national-assembly-2010-2015","dt_team_category-6th-national-assembly-2015-2020","dt_team_category-7th-national-assembly-2020-2025","dt_team_category-105","dt_team_category-104","dt_team_category-92","description-off"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/dt_team\/2374","targetH